1 to i ssue the certified list or certificate of election shall, at a
2 public meeting of the board and in the presence of the candidates
3 involved or their designee, if they or any of them desire to be
4 present, select the nominee or electee by lot.
5 B. C. When a nominee or electee is to be selected by lot
6 pursuant to the provisions of this section, the following procedures
7 shall be observed:
8 1. The secretary of the appropriate election board shall, on or
9 before the tenth day following the second election, notify each of
10 the tying candidates for which the vote was tied. The notice shall
11 include the time, date and location of the selection, shall be made
12 in writing by registered or certified mail and shall be postmarked
13 not fewer than five (5) days prior to the meeting;
14 2. A candidate may designate one person as a witness to attend
15 the meeting on the candidate's behalf. The designation shall be
16 made in writing, signed by the candidate and presented to the
17 secretary of the appropriate election board;
18 3. The secretary of the appropriate election board shall, in
19 full view of those present at the meeting, clearly write or print
20 the name of each tied candidate on separate pieces of paper
21 measuring approximately equal size. The names of the candidates
22 shall be written or printed on the same color and type of paper.
23 The papers shall be folded in half one time so that the written
